Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.84,0:00:43.92,Default,Ere,0000,0000,0000,,I'll bandage your wounds. You'll feel \Nsome discomfort, but please bear with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.64,0:00:46.89,Default,Ere,0000,0000,0000,,This should suffice for the time being.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.42,0:00:49.56,Default,Zes,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.56,0:00:51.85,Default,Ere,0000,0000,0000,,I used to be a Field Medic.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.85,0:00:55.10,Default,Ere,0000,0000,0000,,My apologies, but I'm only \Nversed in emergency first-aid.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.87,0:00:59.29,Default,Ere,0000,0000,0000,,Once we return to Irios, you can seek \Nsome more sophisticated treatment.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.76,0:01:02.88,Default,Zes,0000,0000,0000,,Erekt, what happened to Cleo?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.26,0:01:09.32,Default,Ere,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, but I wasn't able to confirm her condition.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.16,0:01:23.84,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,General True uses most of his own money to support the orphanage.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.76,0:01:28.98,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,Did you grow up there as well?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.64,0:01:35.51,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Moving right along, you need to be \Ndevoting your time to mastering the Delphine!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.16,0:01:40.40,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,I know. I can't even ride a motorcycle, \Nso the Delphine's all I can rely on.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.65,0:01:44.39,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,Since I'm not that keen on dying.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.39,0:01:46.71,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,And I don't care to be lectured by a war child anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.75,0:01:50.29,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Why you... And you call yourself a man of Krisna?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.29,0:01:52.32,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you have any balls?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.73,0:01:54.71,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,Wanna check?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.71,0:01:56.96,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You imbecile!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.75,0:02:13.15,Default,Cle,0000,0000,0000,,The shutters can be open and closed via quartz ligaments...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.90,0:02:20.63,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you think the stars are breathtaking tonight?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.63,0:02:22.01,Default,Cle,0000,0000,0000,,Not really.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.29,0:02:31.44,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,These are blueprints for Golems and the like.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.90,0:02:35.90,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,You don't want to look through your enemy's secret files?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.69,0:02:40.44,Default,Cle,0000,0000,0000,,Even if I did, I wouldn't be \Nable to make sense of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.30,0:02:49.53,Default,Cle,0000,0000,0000,,And besides, well, I'm not really looking for anything like that...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.23,0:02:57.00,Default,Cle,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, why would you leave me \Nalone in here after I stole your gun?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.00,0:02:59.61,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,Would you prefer the torture chamber?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.61,0:03:01.05,Default,Cle,0000,0000,0000,,That's not what I mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.05,0:03:05.88,Default,Cle,0000,0000,0000,,I betrayed your trust and tried to kill your friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.88,0:03:07.19,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed you did.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.25,0:03:10.46,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,But I realized something then.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.46,0:03:12.79,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,You've never killed anyone before, am I right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.94,0:03:17.16,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,I have no complaints with you staying here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.16,0:03:19.60,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,You're free to make yourself at home.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.02,0:03:29.56,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,But if you try to hurt Rygart \Nagain, I won't be so forgiving.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.76,0:03:33.82,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,Now then...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.27,0:03:35.79,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,Can you eat fish?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.79,0:03:36.44,Default,Cle,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.44,0:03:38.00,Default,Cle,0000,0000,0000,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.00,0:03:41.26,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,Then let's have supper underneath the stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.30,0:05:32.69,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,General True! Explain this formation!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.11,0:05:35.84,Default,Tru,0000,0000,0000,,Calm down, Narvi. Just hear me out!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.84,0:05:38.45,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,I'm asking BECAUSE I've already heard!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.01,0:05:43.13,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,You're deploying almost all of the \Nwestern border defense personnel...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.13,0:05:46.62,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,So why am only I being placed on standby in the capital!?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.62,0:05:48.31,Default,Tru,0000,0000,0000,,Like I said, just relax!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.31,0:05:50.05,Default,Tru,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not excluding you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.05,0:05:52.42,Default,Tru,0000,0000,0000,,You're just going to depart a little later than we are.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.16,0:05:56.16,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,So you're telling me to let \Nyou run about unsupervised?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.30,0:05:59.10,Default,Tru,0000,0000,0000,,That's not a very nice way to put it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.10,0:06:02.50,Default,Tru,0000,0000,0000,,I've been a general since before you were even born!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.50,0:06:06.18,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,You're helpless without me around!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.84,0:06:09.13,Default,Tru,0000,0000,0000,,Have you calmed down yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.37,0:06:13.78,Default,Tru,0000,0000,0000,,I would very much like to have you with me,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.78,0:06:18.06,Default,Tru,0000,0000,0000,,but I've volunteered my youngest \Nand finest soldier for something else.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.60,0:06:20.70,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Volunteered?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.38,0:06:24.15,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,The 1st Autonomous Squadron...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.51,0:06:25.37,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,Correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.37,0:06:27.61,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,Your mission will essentially be national defense.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.61,0:06:31.70,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,But you will act as an elite commando unit \Nunder the direct control of the King himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.27,0:06:35.85,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,Heavy Knight 1st Class Narvi, \Nyou've been designated as captain.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.85,0:06:36.50,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.93,0:06:41.57,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,That's quite a lot of authority, and the \Nopportunity to prove myself isn't bad either.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.57,0:06:43.95,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,I might even be able to enter General True's direct command someday.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.95,0:06:46.05,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,Your team will consist of...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.05,0:06:48.05,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,Heavy Knight High Class Nyle.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.05,0:06:53.68,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,Will you be able to follow Captain Narvi's orders though she is your younger sister?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.68,0:06:54.31,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,I will.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.98,0:07:00.40,Default,Nil,0000,0000,0000,,She may be somewhat crude, but I will \Nconsider her orders yours, and give it 110%.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.85,0:07:02.75,Default,Nil,0000,0000,0000,,I am SO lucky!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.75,0:07:08.28,Default,Nil,0000,0000,0000,,Not only is my departure to the front lines delayed, \Nbut I get to gaze upon a bespectacled Lady Sigyn!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.28,0:07:11.81,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,Heavy Knight High Class Loggin. Thank you for your support.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.81,0:07:12.53,Default,Log,0000,0000,0000,,Yes ma'am!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.27,0:07:16.20,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,Heavy Knight High Class Rygart.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.74,0:07:19.03,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,Please follow Captain Narvi's commands.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.03,0:07:20.32,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,You got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.32,0:07:22.27,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,I just gotta do as I'm told, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.99,0:07:29.22,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Rygart, carrying our personal \Ngrudges into battle leads to trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.22,0:07:32.18,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,If you need to get something off your chest, now's the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.62,0:07:35.03,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Oh, I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.97,0:07:43.83,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,So if Captain Narvi demands to see my \Njewels, I suppose I've got no choice, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.86,0:07:48.49,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,If you ever show them to me, I'll blow a hole in them.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.49,0:07:50.90,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,You mean to tell me this has happened before?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.65,0:07:54.82,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,Lady Sigyn snapped...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.13,0:08:00.13,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,Counting the soldier not currently present, \Nthis squad will consist of five people.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.13,0:08:03.11,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,And regarding the fifth member.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.11,0:08:07.06,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,It's still not official, and I myself am opposed to the decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.06,0:08:11.43,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,But as per the Chief of Staff's strong request, Girghe will--
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.43,0:08:12.76,Default,All,0000,0000,0000,,Girghe!?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.47,0:08:19.21,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, what's going on!?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.21,0:08:21.10,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,Girghe, he...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.15,0:08:27.29,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,Knock it off!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.29,0:08:28.45,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,Who the hell do you think you are!?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.65,0:08:34.41,Default,Gir,0000,0000,0000,,Impressive dodging.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.41,0:08:38.50,Default,Gir,0000,0000,0000,,I'd rate you over 60 points in defense, but less than 80.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.35,0:08:41.16,Default,Gir,0000,0000,0000,,There are several weapons before you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.42,0:08:47.33,Default,Gir,0000,0000,0000,,Pick whichever you like.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.99,0:08:53.59,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,Quit screwing around! Like you're giving me a choice!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.13,0:09:13.93,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,He sliced the quartz in two!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.37,0:09:21.08,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,Give it a rest already!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.17,0:09:30.13,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,You fucking psychopath!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.71,0:09:38.58,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,It broke...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.90,0:09:43.49,Default,Gir,0000,0000,0000,,I  figured as much.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.19,0:09:48.94,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,Shit!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.31,0:09:53.73,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,This is bad!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.85,0:10:07.29,Default,Gir,0000,0000,0000,,Very impressive.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.29,0:10:09.62,Default,Gir,0000,0000,0000,,I have to reevaluate your defense.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.62,0:10:12.67,Default,Gir,0000,0000,0000,,Above 70 points, but less than 150.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.67,0:10:14.05,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,You asshole!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.09,0:10:15.76,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,Crap!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.09,0:10:38.16,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Sir Girghe, I don't recall approving of any such exercises.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.16,0:10:40.04,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,But please allow me to participate as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.47,0:10:44.63,Default,Gir,0000,0000,0000,,That was the optimal position to fire from, Lady Narvi.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.63,0:10:46.95,Default,Gir,0000,0000,0000,,So very textbook, it makes me sick.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.62,0:10:53.79,Default,Gir,0000,0000,0000,,Loggin, your attacks are much too predictable.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.74,0:10:58.55,Default,Gir,0000,0000,0000,,But your exemplary covering fire has sealed my escape.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.74,0:11:00.25,Default,Gir,0000,0000,0000,,And now...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.33,0:11:17.03,Default,Nil,0000,0000,0000,,If I didn't stop, your golem would be short a head.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.99,0:11:20.11,Default,Nil,0000,0000,0000,,...and I would've been killed instantly.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.78,0:11:25.91,Default,Nil,0000,0000,0000,,There's only one outcome for us Heavy Knights, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.21,0:11:36.09,Default,Gir,0000,0000,0000,,I've no desire to fight you blind, Sir Nyle.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.09,0:11:39.39,Default,Gir,0000,0000,0000,,Breaking in this Golem has \Nmade for excellent practice.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.53,0:11:44.72,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,This guy is my subordinate?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.72,0:11:48.04,Default,Nil,0000,0000,0000,,Whew... That was a close one.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.67,0:11:56.57,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell is his problem?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.12,0:12:18.55,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,He made a clean cut, but I couldn't do the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.85,0:12:21.98,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,Rygart.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.84,0:12:29.35,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,Is it true you support Girghe being in your squad?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.32,0:12:35.15,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, but my approval alone doesn't mean anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.02,0:12:39.28,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,But why? He's a bigger threat than our enemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.28,0:12:40.25,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,True.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.25,0:12:41.07,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,True?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.47,0:12:48.14,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,That may be true, but I vowed to do \Nwhatever it takes to drive off Athens.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.69,0:13:02.49,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,It'll be fine. Just you watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.01,0:13:08.55,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa... They stretch...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.82,0:13:35.20,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,So you guys march tomorrow, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.20,0:13:35.79,Default,Bal,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.63,0:13:38.47,Default,Bal,0000,0000,0000,,You were at the graveyard this morning, weren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.85,0:13:41.38,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,No, must've been someone else.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.24,0:13:45.31,Default,Bal,0000,0000,0000,,Don't force yourself to carry the burden for other's deaths.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.31,0:13:47.31,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,I told you, you've got the wrong guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.96,0:13:49.73,Default,Bal,0000,0000,0000,,Do I now?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.15,0:13:51.08,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,Yep.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.13,0:13:54.19,Default,Bal,0000,0000,0000,,I see you've met your fifth member.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.19,0:13:56.97,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, but I wouldn't exactly say we "met".
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.97,0:13:58.33,Default,Bal,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.33,0:14:00.17,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,I just don't understand the guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.85,0:14:01.89,Default,Bal,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.18,0:14:05.50,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,He must have a screw loose or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.94,0:14:08.16,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,He used to be a prisoner.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.91,0:14:14.76,Default,Bal,0000,0000,0000,,I was opposed to releasing him myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.57,0:14:18.89,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,Seems like everybody hates him.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.89,0:14:21.57,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,But I suppose he is pretty messed up.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.57,0:14:24.80,Default,Bal,0000,0000,0000,,Last year, he killed several \Ncomrades during a training exercise.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.43,0:14:28.01,Default,Bal,0000,0000,0000,,For no reason whatsoever.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.01,0:14:29.23,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,None at all?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.13,0:14:33.89,Default,Bal,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not really sure how his mind works.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.30,0:14:35.98,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,Was he one of your men?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.98,0:14:36.81,Default,Bal,0000,0000,0000,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.71,0:14:40.47,Default,Bal,0000,0000,0000,,He's my son.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.22,0:14:44.96,Default,Bal,0000,0000,0000,,Do NOT trust him, you hear me?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.96,0:14:45.90,Default,Bal,0000,0000,0000,,No matter what!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.43,0:14:50.32,Default,Bal,0000,0000,0000,,If he acts the least bit suspicious, don't hesitate to kill him!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.71,0:14:56.66,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,Forget it!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.24,0:14:59.33,Default,Bal,0000,0000,0000,,I'll take full responsibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.33,0:15:00.31,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,Not happening!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.31,0:15:02.08,Default,Bal,0000,0000,0000,,If you don't, you'll wind up dead yourself!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.08,0:15:02.88,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,I said forget it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.88,0:15:03.39,Default,Bal,0000,0000,0000,,He...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.39,0:15:04.29,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,NO!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.14,0:15:10.40,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,No parent should ask someone to kill their own child.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.32,0:15:15.05,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,If you want him dead, then do it yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.84,0:15:17.92,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,Make up your mind by the next time we meet.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.92,0:15:19.85,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,Decide if you're gonna kill him or talk it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.71,0:15:27.32,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,Stay alive until then, Pops!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.25,0:15:33.01,Default,Bal,0000,0000,0000,,I will...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.06,0:15:46.84,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,General True, don't do anything stupid!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.91,0:16:16.83,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Since you can't use pressure guns, you'll \Nhave to rely on throwing weapons!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.44,0:16:19.45,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Focus your aim!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.64,0:16:32.05,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,If you don't improve your CQC, \Nyou'll die a hundred times over!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.63,0:16:33.92,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Your defense sucks!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.14,0:16:39.09,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,Hodr!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.55,0:16:41.27,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Hodr!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.09,0:16:44.26,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,Don't make that face.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.26,0:16:47.19,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,I'll come back unharmed for sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.69,0:16:54.26,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,So I want you to promise me, Hodr...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.07,0:17:00.54,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you dare surrender under those ridiculous conditions. At least wait for me to return.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.42,0:17:03.76,Default,Hod,0000,0000,0000,,Alright.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.76,0:17:05.21,Default,Hod,0000,0000,0000,,I've made up my mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.26,0:17:12.38,Default,Hod,0000,0000,0000,,Until you come back, I'll put aside our \Ndifferences with Orlando and seek military aid.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.68,0:17:50.82,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,Tomorrow's the day...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.80,0:18:14.07,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,You leave tomorrow, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.04,0:18:19.01,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. I'm actually kind of sad that I gotta leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.66,0:18:21.82,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,What'll you do when you return home?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.82,0:18:24.45,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,I have to help my dad out on the farm,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.45,0:18:27.83,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,so I guess it's back to the life of a dirty peasant for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.83,0:18:30.32,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,Oh well. It was fun while it lasted.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.98,0:18:32.79,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,I-I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.79,0:18:33.95,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,Good luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.56,0:18:36.30,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,You keep at it here, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.65,0:18:39.51,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,You'll become a first-rate magician. I just know it!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.21,0:18:41.41,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,First-rate...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.41,0:18:44.44,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,You bet! You'll be the commoner's star of hope!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.44,0:18:47.39,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,You'll be the best magician in the entire palace!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.87,0:18:58.07,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,I... don't really care about being top class...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.21,0:19:02.16,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,All I really want... is someone to buy me books every now and then.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.16,0:19:06.61,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,Or someone to take me to the library once a month or so. That's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.37,0:19:13.79,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,So I wouldn't really mind marrying say... a farmer...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.79,0:19:15.47,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? What'd you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.36,0:19:19.59,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,Don't mumble like that. Speak up so I can hear you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.85,0:19:22.27,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,...never mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.05,0:19:25.02,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, okay then.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.02,0:19:25.72,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,See you 'round!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.15,0:19:35.82,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,I really... wouldn't mind...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.32,0:20:00.04,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,He leaves today.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.88,0:20:26.62,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,Good morning. Today's the day, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.05,0:20:29.91,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,Y-yeah, it sure is.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.70,0:20:34.17,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong? Are you angry about something?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.56,0:20:35.83,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not angry.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.20,0:20:38.41,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,But I am upset.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.13,0:20:40.03,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,Okayyy...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.54,0:20:42.25,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,So why are you upset?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.25,0:20:43.45,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,I don't wanna talk about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.45,0:20:46.03,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,Did I do something?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.03,0:20:47.94,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,It isn't your fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.76,0:20:50.32,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,But you're still upset?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.32,0:20:51.06,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.59,0:20:54.10,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I'm stumped.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.92,0:20:57.77,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,If I die out there, it'll haunt you in your sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.77,0:21:00.19,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,What can I do to cheer you up?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.19,0:21:01.36,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,"Die"...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.42,0:21:08.74,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,If you come back unharmed, I'll stop being angry.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.24,0:21:10.16,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.74,0:21:13.83,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,If you come back unharmed, I'll stop being angry.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.09,0:21:19.35,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,Alright, you got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.17,0:21:22.80,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,Fall back to the left!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.17,0:21:26.06,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,They've blocked our retreat!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.06,0:21:27.93,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,At least save the General!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.56,0:22:03.99,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,What was that noise?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.12,0:22:21.49,Default,Col,0000,0000,0000,,Nicely done.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.55,0:22:26.78,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,What!? General True's battalion was ambushed by Athens?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.17,0:22:28.48,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,That's impossible!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.48,0:22:32.45,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,It's still 30 thousand Mehl to the border. \NWhy would they be ambushed here!?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.94,0:22:34.85,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,Did they slip through the border somehow?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.85,0:22:37.35,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,What happened to the True Battalion?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.53,0:22:39.88,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,It was almost completely annihilated.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.45,0:22:45.23,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,General True... Perished in battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.08,0:23:18.83,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Millennium Corps, moving out!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.50,0:23:44.37,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,I've received your report.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.37,0:23:46.61,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,Splendid work, Colonel Io.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.61,0:23:49.95,Default,Io,0000,0000,0000,,My men and I cannot take all the credit for this victory.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.95,0:23:53.28,Default,Io,0000,0000,0000,,Furthermore, the enemy's resistance \Nis fiercer than we anticipated.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.70,0:23:57.04,Default,Io,0000,0000,0000,,We lost several of our finest soldiers.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.69,0:24:01.50,Default,Gen,0000,0000,0000,,You dispatched nearly 50 units from the enemy's main forces.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.50,0:24:03.20,Default,Gen,0000,0000,0000,,Those men did not die in vain.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.32,0:24:07.13,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,We've received permission to take a short break.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.30,0:24:11.99,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,Your unit's been pushed especially hard, so let them rest for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.99,0:24:12.68,Default,Io,0000,0000,0000,,Sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.03,0:24:20.81,Default,Nike,0000,0000,0000,,You guys are pathetic!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.81,0:24:24.98,Default,Nike,0000,0000,0000,,Women don't like guys with such low stamina!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.62,0:24:29.03,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,Piss off. Don't go comparing us to a freak like you.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.76,0:24:33.91,Default,Nike,0000,0000,0000,,Aren't you all frustrated that a dainty \Nlittle gal like me stole your thunder?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.91,0:24:36.73,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,"Gal" my ass, you 25-year-old midget!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.14,0:24:47.75,Default,Nike,0000,0000,0000,,25 years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.75,0:24:49.94,Default,Nike,0000,0000,0000,,Still. Makes. Me. A.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.94,0:24:51.41,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,A y-y-y-young--
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.41,0:24:52.55,Default,Nike,0000,0000,0000,,Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.00,0:24:54.41,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,A young lady!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.01,0:24:55.84,Default,Io,0000,0000,0000,,Nike!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.61,0:24:58.89,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,My ear! MY EAR!!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.25,0:25:06.06,Default,Nik,0000,0000,0000,,I was so scared, Colonel! Really, really scared!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.44,0:25:07.92,Default,Nik,0000,0000,0000,,But I tried my absolute hardest!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.92,0:25:10.31,Default,Io,0000,0000,0000,,I-Indeed. Good work.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.31,0:25:13.35,Default,Nik,0000,0000,0000,,Are you proud? Am I a good girl?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.35,0:25:15.01,Default,Io,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.01,0:25:16.54,Default,Io,0000,0000,0000,,You took an enemy General's head.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.54,0:25:20.29,Default,Io,0000,0000,0000,,Once we return, I'm certain you'll be awarded a medal of honor for your achievements.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.66,0:25:23.63,Default,Nik,0000,0000,0000,,Then... Can I have my usual reward?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.63,0:25:28.65,Default,Nik,0000,0000,0000,,I wanna be praised by you Colonel, even more than \NSecretary General Loquis or General Borcuse.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.00,0:25:36.40,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,Pardon me, Colonel.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.40,0:25:41.04,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,We did receive permission to rest, but is it really \Nprudent to do so in the middle of enemy territory?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.04,0:25:44.10,Default,Io,0000,0000,0000,,It's fine. The general's forces are \Nkeeping watch for us, so rest assured.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.49,0:25:51.14,Default,Io,0000,0000,0000,,We've been marching for 25 hours \Nstraight. I imagine we're at our limits.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.14,0:25:55.40,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,It will likely take about six hours for the \Nenemy remnants to retreat to their army.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.73,0:25:57.70,Default,Io,0000,0000,0000,,You have precisely four hours to rest!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.70,0:26:00.83,Default,Io,0000,0000,0000,,After that, we resume our attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.23,0:26:06.15,Default,Io,0000,0000,0000,,We'll crush Baldr! And then the war will be over!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.16,0:26:14.09,Default,Io,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,1500)\i1}Krisnan Kingdom's Arracan Desert
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.78,0:26:16.71,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,That's the signal from our scouts!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.71,0:26:19.89,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,Athens forces spotted! Estimated 50 units!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.89,0:26:24.39,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,50 Golems?! That's 20 less than we've got!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.82,0:26:28.15,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,Captain Elsa! Let's swarm the enemy!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.15,0:26:29.43,Default,Els,0000,0000,0000,,Restrain yourself!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.43,0:26:31.54,Default,Els,0000,0000,0000,,Wait for General Baldr's orders!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.40,0:26:34.47,Default,Bal,0000,0000,0000,,Prepare to intercept them with your Pressure Guns!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.47,0:26:37.80,Default,Bal,0000,0000,0000,,We've got the high ground! \NDo not leave your positions!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.80,0:26:38.86,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,Yes sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.25,0:26:42.80,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,Krisnan forces spotted. Approximately 70 in number.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.97,0:26:52.48,Default,Io,0000,0000,0000,,They're in perfect position to meet our \Nattack. Impressive as usual, General Baldr.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.96,0:26:56.15,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,Charge.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.15,0:26:58.36,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,All units, commence operation!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.28,0:27:02.93,Default,Bal,0000,0000,0000,,Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.19,0:27:14.49,Default,Els,0000,0000,0000,,They're attempting a Pincer?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.49,0:27:17.24,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,General, Captain Elsa, over there!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.65,0:27:27.00,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,You can see from here? Is that really him?!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.00,0:27:32.00,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. It distinctly resembles the Commander's \NGolem that we spotted crossing the border.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.00,0:27:32.92,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,Impossible...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.51,0:27:34.88,Default,Els,0000,0000,0000,,General Baldr.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.74,0:27:40.43,Default,Bal,0000,0000,0000,,Forget it, Elsa. It's a blatant challenge!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.43,0:27:42.18,Default,Els,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I believe it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.18,0:27:42.84,Default,Els,0000,0000,0000,,However...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.35,0:27:47.36,Default,Els,0000,0000,0000,,Staring each other down like \Nthis could cost us valuable time.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.36,0:27:50.27,Default,Els,0000,0000,0000,,If we don't act now, we'll never have a chance like this again.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.59,0:27:55.19,Default,Els,0000,0000,0000,,Please lend me 10 Golems before their reinforcements arrive.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.41,0:28:01.09,Default,Bal,0000,0000,0000,,Alright. Take 20.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.09,0:28:05.54,Default,Bal,0000,0000,0000,,But you're to retreat immediately at the first sign of danger!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.08,0:28:06.99,Default,Bal,0000,0000,0000,,Understood?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.37,0:28:08.21,Default,Els,0000,0000,0000,,Yes sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.52,0:28:18.95,Default,Els,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on here?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.67,0:28:21.22,Default,Els,0000,0000,0000,,All units, open fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.71,0:28:41.74,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,What a spectacular attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.26,0:28:47.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A classic blitz maneuver.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.45,0:28:58.21,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,However, your misdirected attack \Ndidn't turn out like you had expected.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.47,0:29:06.93,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,Such is war. Your carefully \Ncalculated decision has backfired.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.53,0:29:21.82,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,A clear head can be just as much of a hindrance.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.82,0:29:23.86,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,A lesson you've just learned the hard way.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.44,0:29:43.81,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,E-Elsa squad... annihilated.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.83,0:29:48.66,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,A mere six golems defeated Elsa {\i1}and{\i0} 20 of ours!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.60,0:29:53.91,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,A-And Athens' didn't reform their ranks!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.91,0:29:57.73,Default,SOl,0000,0000,0000,,Those bastards didn't even bother protecting their commander!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.31,0:30:00.86,Default,Bal,0000,0000,0000,,No, they didn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.29,0:30:03.87,Default,Bal,0000,0000,0000,,They simply stood by... and watched our jaws drop.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.44,0:30:10.12,Default,Bal,0000,0000,0000,,Elsa losing to a mere six golems, and \Nthe bizarre actions of their flanks...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.12,0:30:13.24,Default,Bal,0000,0000,0000,,It's no wonder the men are terrified.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.24,0:30:18.62,Default,Bal,0000,0000,0000,,Borcuse... Did you plan to gamble for this outcome from the start?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.02,0:30:24.78,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,General Baldr, you always \Nmake such rational decisions.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.78,0:30:27.42,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,But that is your one and only strength!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.42,0:30:31.56,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,My men do not fear opponents who think rationally.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.47,0:30:36.83,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,Fear deals a crippling blow to soldiers.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.83,0:30:40.45,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,Be it a single man, or a force of one \Nmillion soldiers, it makes no difference.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.45,0:30:43.62,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,Man can deny neither hunger nor fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.10,0:30:46.74,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,Nike. You may begin.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.85,0:30:50.62,Default,Nik,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, but sir...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.62,0:30:55.79,Default,Io,0000,0000,0000,,General, I do not feel that such actions are necessary!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.79,0:30:57.75,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,They are.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.75,0:30:59.29,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,Do it, Nike.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.77,0:31:02.04,Default,Nik,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, Colonel.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.84,0:31:07.39,Default,Nik,0000,0000,0000,,Oh well, she's already dead anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.74,0:31:10.17,Default,Nik,0000,0000,0000,,Technically, you could just call this disassembly!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.48,0:31:17.48,Default,Bal,0000,0000,0000,,Borcuse...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.72,0:31:26.11,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,That's Captain Elsa's...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.24,0:31:35.98,Default,Sol{faint},0000,0000,0000,,Captain Elsa...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.43,0:31:45.55,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,Your men are panicking.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.55,0:31:49.13,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,And you'll come under fire \Nwhether you charge or retreat.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.47,0:31:53.38,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,At this juncture, it's already checkmate for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.35,0:31:58.70,Default,Bal,0000,0000,0000,,Forgive me, Elsa.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.34,0:32:02.26,Default,Bal,0000,0000,0000,,All units, CHARGE!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.53,0:32:08.19,Default,Bal,0000,0000,0000,,Did I stutter? All golems, prepare to attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.19,0:32:11.12,Default,Bal,0000,0000,0000,,Reconnaissance, Supply Teams, and Infantry, standby!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.12,0:32:13.03,Default,Bal,0000,0000,0000,,Kill every last enemy before you!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.03,0:32:15.20,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,B-But sir, the enemy's...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.20,0:32:16.76,Default,Bal,0000,0000,0000,,Alright! Let's move!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.38,0:32:19.95,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.95,0:32:22.13,Default,Sol{x4},0000,0000,0000,,Roger!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.13,0:32:25.01,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,Let's take back the Captain's remains!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:30.37,0:32:32.08,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,They've rallied their spirits.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.08,0:32:34.63,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,Victory is officially ours.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.63,0:32:35.67,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.15,0:32:39.33,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,However, the soldiers' fear has transformed into rage.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.33,0:32:42.51,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,They'll likely fight to their dying breath.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.30,0:32:48.44,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,General Baldr, you're so \Nstraightforward it makes me sick.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.35,0:32:53.05,Default,Io,0000,0000,0000,,Moving to intercept.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.05,0:32:57.69,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,Colonel Io. We'll continue our discussion later.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.69,0:33:00.97,Default,Io,0000,0000,0000,,I appreciate your concern, but I have no need for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.50,0:33:02.30,Default,Io,0000,0000,0000,,Move out!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.30,0:33:03.13,Default,Nik,0000,0000,0000,,Roger!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.07,0:33:18.11,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,What the fuck is our left flank doing!?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.11,0:33:19.58,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,Just ignore their rear guard!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.08,0:33:24.14,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,At this rate, we can't link up with the right flank!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.14,0:33:25.90,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,We'll make a detour and pursue the enemy's main forces!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.75,0:33:31.57,Default,Bal,0000,0000,0000,,Borcuse!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.71,0:33:48.87,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,All that's left is to wait for their \Nseparated flanks to enter firing range.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.87,0:33:49.83,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.83,0:33:50.63,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,The day is ours.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.55,0:33:56.01,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,God dammit! We're not finished yet, Athens!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.01,0:33:58.19,Default,Bal,0000,0000,0000,,Bolster your defenses! Here they come!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.71,0:33:59.84,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,Alright, fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.98,0:34:12.59,Default,Bal,0000,0000,0000,,Don't retreat! Just leave it to the rear support!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.59,0:34:14.49,Default,Bal,0000,0000,0000,,Not yet! Hold on a little longer!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.55,0:34:18.26,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,They're holding out pretty well!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.26,0:34:20.04,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna earn myself a medal today!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.74,0:34:29.54,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,Colonel! Hostile to our left!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.68,0:34:39.01,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,F-Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.79,0:34:45.31,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,Stand your ground!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.11,0:34:56.79,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,General Baldr! The enemy's left side ceased their attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.13,0:35:00.51,Default,Bal,0000,0000,0000,,Is it Rygart?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.51,0:35:02.91,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,The left side's being decimated by the enemy!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.91,0:35:05.83,Default,Nik,0000,0000,0000,,Dammit, left flank! Get it together!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.83,0:35:08.75,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,Just... one hostile?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.75,0:35:11.54,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, it is indeed a single unit.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.76,0:35:15.44,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,Hmph. Krisna certainly has \Nsome interesting characters.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.44,0:35:20.19,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,Bardess! What kind of man laughs as he watches his comrades die?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.19,0:35:22.96,Default,Bar,0000,0000,0000,,Sir! I was merely laughing at my own comment.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.47,0:35:26.64,Default,Bar,0000,0000,0000,,I'm terribly sorry, General Borcuse.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.64,0:35:28.73,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,Do you understand, Rygart?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.34,0:35:32.73,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,Once the third layer of armor's been compromised,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.73,0:35:34.95,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,you may treat it as if the frame itself has been damaged.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.95,0:35:37.56,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,At that point, you're to purge the armor and withdraw.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.35,0:35:40.81,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,I'm already down to my last layer.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.81,0:35:44.94,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,But... I have no choice!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.94,0:35:47.83,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,I have to become a cold-blooded killer!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.34,0:35:55.05,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,He stopped me!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.12,0:36:07.88,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.80,0:36:14.36,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,Dammit! Purge or not, the armor's not gonna last any longer!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.49,0:36:20.40,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,W-What the hell kind of jump is that!?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.40,0:36:33.88,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,Guard your vital points and close the distance!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.88,0:36:36.63,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,Shit, the nail darts aren't cutting it.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.63,0:36:38.30,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,Just piercing them isn't good enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.88,0:36:40.05,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,Aim for his landing point!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.87,0:36:48.43,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,Scatter! We're being sniped!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.42,0:36:54.14,Default,Log,0000,0000,0000,,That's enough, Rygart! Now fall back!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.00,0:36:58.89,Default,Nil,0000,0000,0000,,Hey Narvi, that tremor just now was from the Delphine's landing!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.89,0:37:00.07,Default,Nil,0000,0000,0000,,They've already started!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.99,0:37:03.41,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,We were supposed to initiate the attack...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.41,0:37:07.53,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Loggin and Rygart's team had more \Ndistance to cover. Just what IS that golem?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.37,0:37:12.41,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Nyle, enemy spotted!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.41,0:37:13.44,Default,Nil,0000,0000,0000,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.11,0:37:16.75,Default,Nil,0000,0000,0000,,We can't pull off a rear attack, \Nbut we can come in from the side!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.75,0:37:19.67,Default,Nil,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like 23 units out there. You sure about this?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.67,0:37:24.11,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Of course! While Baldr acts as a decoy, our squad will take them down!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.11,0:37:27.80,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,It's the ideal situation. I can make \Na splendid report to General True!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.80,0:37:29.09,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Begin the attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:33.09,0:37:34.96,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Girghe!? What the hell are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.96,0:37:35.95,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,I said begin the attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:39.04,0:37:40.11,Default,Nil,0000,0000,0000,,Girghe!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.89,0:37:45.85,Default,Gir,0000,0000,0000,,I can't do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.07,0:37:47.91,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.56,0:37:51.85,Default,Gir,0000,0000,0000,,My legs are cramping. I can't move!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.48,0:37:55.65,Default,Gir,0000,0000,0000,,I...I'm scared!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.65,0:37:59.86,Default,Gir,0000,0000,0000,,I've never fought in real combat before!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.10,0:38:09.38,Default,Log,0000,0000,0000,,Excellent work, Rygart.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.23,0:38:14.61,Default,Log,0000,0000,0000,,The enemy's left formation has collapsed. \NGeneral Baldr's forces have begun regrouping.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.87,0:38:23.29,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,This thing's only got six minutes of juice left.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:28.53,0:38:30.26,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Is this your idea of a joke, Girghe!?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.26,0:38:31.45,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,You're {\i1}scared{\i0} !?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:31.91,0:38:33.88,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Since when have you been such a spineless pansy?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.88,0:38:35.64,Default,Nil,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, c'mon man.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.64,0:38:38.53,Default,Nil,0000,0000,0000,,Show us that same strength you tried to kill us with!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.53,0:38:40.57,Default,Nil,0000,0000,0000,,More like we're screwed if you don't...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.54,0:38:46.47,Default,Gir,0000,0000,0000,,T-That was during training! I knew the exact number of enemies!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.47,0:38:49.59,Default,Gir,0000,0000,0000,,And besides, that was just a mock battle!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.65,0:38:56.35,Default,Nil,0000,0000,0000,,We're in trouble, Narvi! The enemy's spotted us!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.31,0:39:00.21,Default,Nil,0000,0000,0000,,Our surprise attack's a bust. Should we retreat?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.21,0:39:05.09,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,No, the enemy's still disorganized! You and I can still break through!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.09,0:39:07.54,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Baldr's already noticed us and begun moving!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.54,0:39:09.28,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,We'll launch a pincer attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.28,0:39:10.63,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Move out!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.36,0:39:12.38,Default,Nil,0000,0000,0000,,Roger that!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.05,0:39:24.81,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,A golem with a broken blade for a horn that disrupted our tactics...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.55,0:39:31.25,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,It's a complete mystery to us, but it's \Npower and mobility are astounding.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:31.25,0:39:34.48,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,I guess I could call it the {\i1}Broken Blade{\i0} for the time being.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.66,0:39:42.69,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,That's... Borcuse?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:44.78,0:39:47.28,Default,Nik,0000,0000,0000,,Colonel, the enemy's retreating!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.28,0:39:48.77,Default,Io,0000,0000,0000,,Damn you, Baldr.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.77,0:39:50.44,Default,Io,0000,0000,0000,,He was trying to lure us out.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.90,0:39:55.16,Default,Io,0000,0000,0000,,We can't just watch our right flank be \Nkilled. Very well. You may join them!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.45,0:39:56.65,Default,Nik,0000,0000,0000,,Yes sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.96,0:39:59.92,Default,Bar,0000,0000,0000,,Colonel Io, wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.43,0:40:03.93,Default,Bar,0000,0000,0000,,It is time.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.63,0:40:12.37,Default,Nik,0000,0000,0000,,Aw man, the withdrawal signal?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.57,0:40:16.02,Default,Nil,0000,0000,0000,,You're mine!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.06,0:40:23.40,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Two down!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.22,0:40:29.01,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,All that's left is for Nyle and I to crush the right flank!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.01,0:40:30.95,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't quite go according to plan though.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.95,0:40:32.05,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Perfect!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.37,0:40:36.29,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.47,0:40:40.53,Default,Nil,0000,0000,0000,,Nobody's here.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.45,0:40:46.61,Default,Nil,0000,0000,0000,,Seems like Baldr's team's in pursuit,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.85,0:40:49.13,Default,Nil,0000,0000,0000,,but they're way ahead of us now.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:49.13,0:40:52.55,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,The enemy... retreated?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.86,0:40:57.41,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Dammit! We're late!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.88,0:41:12.19,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,Is he running away?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.70,0:41:18.47,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,Forget it. Once you drop down to five minutes, you \Ncould run out out of power while in enemy range.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.59,0:41:22.25,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Do not{\i0} join the pursuit teams.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.44,0:41:27.96,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,Why do I feel relieved?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.39,0:41:42.23,Default,Cle,0000,0000,0000,,A-Are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:42.63,0:41:44.45,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,Haven't slept in three days, that's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.41,0:41:50.28,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,Attach segment 5-86 with the new rivets...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.01,0:41:55.22,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,Cleo... help me swap out these parts...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.22,0:41:57.44,Default,Cle,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, you mean help you get changed?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.75,0:42:10.86,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.25,0:42:15.63,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,What beautiful, black hair...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.59,0:42:21.85,Default,Cle,0000,0000,0000,,I think blonde hair is prettier.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.85,0:42:23.83,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,You really... think... so?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.85,0:42:30.47,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,Untainted by any other shade. Purely black...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:31.04,0:42:34.54,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,Personally, I... truly admire it.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.16,0:42:45.14,Default,Cle,0000,0000,0000,,She's Zess' friend, just like that man Rygart.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:45.69,0:42:47.05,Default,Cle,0000,0000,0000,,But she's still my enemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:48.27,0:42:49.86,Default,Cle,0000,0000,0000,,I don't understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:52.70,0:42:56.68,Default,Nik,0000,0000,0000,,Retreating while we were crushing them? What a load of crap.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.68,0:42:59.60,Default,Bar,0000,0000,0000,,Nike, this is a strategic withdrawal.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:59.60,0:43:02.64,Default,Bar,0000,0000,0000,,We're merely going to join up with the \Nrear guard and some reinforcements.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.64,0:43:08.22,Default,Nik,0000,0000,0000,,"Strategic withdrawal". That's such a convenient phrase, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.22,0:43:11.73,Default,Nik,0000,0000,0000,,What really happened was you all were \Ngetting worked by the black golem.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:16.95,0:43:18.82,Default,Io,0000,0000,0000,,Nike, stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:27.23,0:43:30.04,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,With just one shot,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:30.04,0:43:33.61,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,he found the ideal angle, the collar's thin \Narmor, and the perfect firing distance.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.43,0:43:41.76,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,Nike! 11 o'clock, 80 degrees!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:50.23,0:43:51.41,Default,Nik,0000,0000,0000,,An Artemis?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.78,0:43:53.02,Default,Io,0000,0000,0000,,Nike, run!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:53.70,0:43:55.94,Default,Nik,0000,0000,0000,,You little prick!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.25,0:44:04.39,Default,Io,0000,0000,0000,,Nike!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:05.62,0:44:07.80,Default,Bar,0000,0000,0000,,He's using her as a human shield!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:07.80,0:44:08.99,Default,Bar,0000,0000,0000,,We can't budge an inch like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:16.29,0:44:18.07,Default,Nik,0000,0000,0000,,Colonel!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:23.86,0:44:26.12,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,He's a dead-eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:27.17,0:44:29.23,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,He's a tough one! Don't go getting picked off now!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.85,0:44:35.07,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,I'll squash you like a bug!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.16,0:44:48.64,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,Oh boy. It sure is nerve-wracking being this high up.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:50.44,0:44:53.17,Default,Log,0000,0000,0000,,Well? Can you see the enemy?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:53.17,0:44:57.81,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,It's fine to rely on the Delphine's eyes, but \Nonce I'm down to a minute, I'm coming down.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:57.81,0:44:59.03,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,Now then.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:05.78,0:45:06.56,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:08.19,0:45:09.14,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,I found them!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:23.20,0:45:24.39,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,Girghe...
